                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.001 L 76/3: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Schurman</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-06-16T16:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 16, 1922—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>148. Your 262 June 15, 8 P.M.</p>
                <p>Department approves suggested procedure merely to acknowledge receipt of note and
                    attend Li’s reception, thus dealing with the situation as a new administration
                    and not a new government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
